  "text": "This analysis identifies the C++ source files in envoyproxy/envoy v1.31.2 that implement HTTP request header injection prevention, validation, and sanitization mechanisms:\n\n## Header Validation Framework\n\nThe primary header validation logic is located in `source/extensions/http/header_validators/envoy_default/` directory, which implements the Universal Header Validator (UHV). Key components include:\n\n1. **Core Validator Classes**: `HeaderValidator` (header_validator.h/cc) provides base validation methods for:\n   - `validateMethodHeader()` - validates HTTP methods against IANA registry\n   - `validateStatusHeader()` - validates response status codes\n   - `validateGenericHeaderName()` and `validateGenericHeaderValue()` - validates any header name/value\n   - `validateContentLengthHeader()` - validates content length format\n   - `validateSchemeHeader()` and `validateHostHeader()` - validates scheme and authority headers\n   - `validatePathHeaderCharacters()` - validates path header characters\n\n2. **Protocol-Specific Validators**:\n   - `Http1HeaderValidator` (http1_header_validator.h/cc) - HTTP/1.1 specific validation including Transfer-Encoding and Content-Length header conflict detection via `validateContentLengthAndTransferEncoding()`\n   - `Http2HeaderValidator` (http2_header_validator.h/cc) - HTTP/2 specific validation with pseudo-header handling\n   - `ServerHttp1HeaderValidator` and `ClientHttp1HeaderValidator` - server/client-side implementations with `sanitizeContentLength()` and request header transformation\n   - `ServerHttp2HeaderValidator` and `ClientHttp2HeaderValidator` - HTTP/2 server/client implementations\n\n## Header Sanitization and Stripping\n\n1. **Connection Manager Utilities** (`source/common/http/conn_manager_utility.h/cc`):\n   - `sanitizeTEHeader()` - removes TE header to prevent header injection via Transfer-Encoding\n   - `cleanInternalHeaders()` - removes internal-only headers from external requests to prevent header injection attacks\n   - `mutateRequestHeaders()` - main header mutation entry point that orchestrates sanitization\n   - Validates via `validateContentLengthAndTransferEncoding()` to prevent header smuggling\n\n2. **Header Utility Functions** (`source/common/http/header_utility.h/cc`):\n   - `stripTrailingHostDot()` - removes trailing dots from Host/Authority headers\n   - `stripPortFromHost()` - removes port information from Host headers\n   - `isEnvoyInternalRequest()` - detects internal requests using x-envoy-internal-request header\n   - `checkValidRequestHeaders()` - validates header keys and values for forbidden characters (NULLs, newlines)\n   - `checkHeaderNameForUnderscores()` - handles headers with underscores based on configuration\n\n3. **Connection Header Sanitization** (`source/common/http/utility.h/cc`):\n   - `sanitizeConnectionHeader()` - implements RFC 7230 section 6.1 compliance by:\n     - Parsing the Connection header\n     - Removing any headers nominated by the Connection header value\n     - Limiting nominated headers to prevent DoS (max 10 headers)\n     - Removing the TE header if empty after sanitization\n\n## Internal Header Stripping\n\n1. **Internal-Only Headers Configuration** (`source/common/router/config_impl.h/cc`):\n   - Manages a configurable list of `internal_only_headers_` that should be stripped from external requests\n   - Defined in route configuration and enforced during request mutation\n   - Prevents internal metadata from leaking to upstream services\n\n2. **Connection Manager Implementation** (`source/common/http/conn_manager_impl.h/cc`):\n   - Tracks `is_internally_created_` flag to distinguish internal vs external requests\n   - Only sanitizes headers on first pass through the connection manager\n   - Uses `cleanInternalHeaders()` to strip headers marked as internal-only\n\n## Character Validation\n\n1. **Character Tables** (`source/extensions/http/header_validators/envoy_default/character_tables.h`):\n   - Defines bit arrays for valid characters in different header components\n   - Used to prevent header injection by rejecting invalid characters\n   - Supports per-protocol validation (HTTP/1.1 vs HTTP/2)\n\n## Path Normalization\n\n1. **Path Normalizer** (`source/extensions/http/header_validators/envoy_default/path_normalizer.h/cc`):\n   - `sanitizePathWithFragment()` - strips fragments from request path\n   - `sanitizeEncodedSlashes()` - handles percent-encoded slash characters\n   - `encodeAdditionalCharactersInPath()` - encodes non-compliant characters in paths\n   - `checkForPercent00InUrlPath()` - prevents null byte injection via percent-encoding\n\n## Configuration and Overrides\n\n1. **Header Validator Configuration** (`source/extensions/http/header_validators/envoy_default/config.h/cc`):\n   - Configurable header validation rules\n   - `restrict_http_methods` - limits HTTP methods to IANA registry\n   - Support for underscore handling in header names\n\n2. **Configuration Overrides** (`source/extensions/http/header_validators/envoy_default/config_overrides.h`):\n   - Runtime overrides for validation behavior\n   - Allows backward compatibility with non-compliant characters\n\n## HTTP Codec Integration\n\n1. **HTTP/1 Codec** (`source/common/http/http1/codec_impl.h/cc`):\n   - Header size limit enforcement\n   - Underscore in header names detection and handling\n   - Integrates with header validators\n\n2. **HTTP/2 Codec** (`source/common/http/http2/codec_impl.h/cc`):\n   - Pseudo-header validation\n   - Stream error handling for invalid headers\n\nThese files collectively implement comprehensive HTTP request header injection prevention through validation at parse time, sanitization of dangerous headers, and removal of internal-only headers before external transmission."
}

